This excerpt is why I thought DI could be calculated that way:<br>
<br>
&quot;Effectively, the weapon's actual damage bonus is the same as my value for DB. The number that is analagous to the mob's max hit is the modal damage for the PC's weapon. Modal damage = DB + 2*(Weapon damage).<br>
So DI is equal to<br>
((DB + 2*(Weapon damage)) - DB)/20<br>
= (Weapon damage)/10<br>
And the min hit is still DB + DI.<br>
<br>
So, with my 30/37 lance, DB = 12 and DI = 30/10 = 3. So my min hit should be 12 + 3 = 15, which it is according to my parser.&quot;<br>
<br>
Thanks for clearing up that this isn't the case - I'll be sure to only do maximum-minimum/19 from now on.<br>
<br>
But this brings up a few questions.<br>
<br>
One, how do I calculate maximum hit? I've heard the formula (((STR+Skill)/100)*weapon damage+damage bonus) before, but I don't know if it's correct. It also would imply that there is some way that STR and Skill affects your damage....which it should, but none of the formulas so far have taken either number into account.<br>
<br>
Two, how do you round when calculating damage? I don't know if the game rounds down, up, or to the nearest whole number, and it seems like it would make a big difference when calculating a few things.<br>
<br>
Three, I don't totally understand you, Graal. Do you mean that after calculating your damage just like the game would calculate a mob's damage, it suddenly throws in a random number to add to that damage, from 0-37? You said 0-37*DI, but that would be a gigantic number to add on...and if it just added 37, my maximum would be my modal 78+37=115, and my maximum is larger than that - 123 was my biggest hit. So I don't understand how that 0-37 number is used.<br>
<br>
But at least it sounds like you know what I'm talking about and have some idea what the answer is <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
